org.springframework.web.reactive.socket.client

Class RxNettyWebSocketClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.springframework.web.reactive.socket.client.WebSocketClientSupport
      • org.springframework.web.reactive.socket.client.RxNettyWebSocketClient
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    WebSocketClient

    public class RxNettyWebSocketClient
extends WebSocketClientSupport
implements WebSocketClient
    WebSocketClient implementation for use with RxNetty.

    Note: RxNetty HttpClient instances require a host and port in order to be created. Hence it is not possible to configure a single HttpClient instance to use upfront. Instead the constructors accept a function for obtaining client instances when establishing a connection to a specific URI. By default new instances are created per connection with a shared Netty EventLoopGroup. See constructors for more details.

    Since:
    5.0
    Author:
    Rossen Stoyanchev

    • Constructor Detail

      • RxNettyWebSocketClient

        public RxNettyWebSocketClient()
        Default constructor that creates HttpClient instances via HttpClient.newClient(String, int) using port 80 or 443 depending on the target URL scheme.

        Note: By default a new HttpClient instance is created per WebSocket connection. Those instances will share a global EventLoopGroup that RxNetty obtains via RxEventLoopProvider.globalClientEventLoop(boolean).
